name: Shilluk Man
description: The Shilluk: Chollo are an important Afro-pastoralist, and Nilotic-speaking people belonging to a part of the larger Luo ethnic group. They reside on both banks of the Upper Nile River, in the vicinity of the city of Malakal in South Sudan. Their population is an estimated 500,000, making them the third largest minority ethnic group of South Sudan. 50% of the proceeds from each sale will be donated to Survival International; an organization dedicated to the protection of tribal rights.
